oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:title: Ritter's Grocery
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:description: Photograph of a group of people posed in front of Ritter's Grocery in Columbia. There are buckets of produce and other goods on display outside the shop. In addition to the Ritter's store signs, there are signs on the front of the business that read "The Big Store," and "White Star Coffee."
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:source: Looking Back at Tennessee Photograph Collection, 1890-1981
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:subject: People; Stores & shops; Advertising
